Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. If you are getting angry because @fields.child_nickname won’t stop crying, it’s okay to leave them on their back in a safe place and walk away for a bit and take a quick pause. Taking a pause will help you respond better. Stay nearby so that you can monitor @fields.child_nickname. Check on @fields.child_nickname every 5-10 minutes.

Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. If you are getting angry because your baby won’t stop crying, it’s okay to leave them on their back in a safe place and walk away for a bit and take a quick pause. Taking a pause will help you respond better. Stay nearby so that you can monitor your baby. Check on your baby every 5-10 minutes.

It is completely normal to feel overwhelmed as a parent. All parents feel this way. Try calling a family member or a friend. Sometimes just talking with someone is enough, but if you still feel overwhelmed, ask someone for help. Calling for help is a sign of strength. You can do this!

You are doing your best!
